    {
      "id": "PopularPost309894",
      "post_content": "Always run next to other burn. This either becomes [Lightning bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning bolt) 5-8 or it grants tremendous tempo advantage in a burn deck. It's weakest attribute is that it requires an opponent's creature to cast it on, meaning it is occasionally a dead card. I love casting it on 4 toughness creatures when other burn is at the ready, because even though it's card disadvantage, it is often enough to threaten their win con and they'll eat 5.  \n  \nAlso runs well with [Vexing Devil](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vexing Devil) simply because one devil, bolt, salvo = 60% of their health. Probably run near [staggershock](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=staggershock). 5 of those in any combination will ruin an opponent by t3-t4. No god draws. Just 5 non-lands and 3 lands.",
      "posted_by": "blurrymadness",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost309894\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">Always run next to other burn. This either becomes <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lightning bolt\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning bolt\">Lightning bolt</a> 5-8 or it grants tremendous tempo advantage in a burn deck. It's weakest attribute is that it requires an opponent's creature to cast it on, meaning it is occasionally a dead card. I love casting it on 4 toughness creatures when other burn is at the ready, because even though it's card disadvantage, it is often enough to threaten their win con and they'll eat 5.<br/><br/>Also runs well with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vexing Devil\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vexing Devil\">Vexing Devil</a> simply because one devil, bolt, salvo = 60% of their health. Probably run near <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"staggershock\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=staggershock\">staggershock</a>. 5 of those in any combination will ruin an opponent by t3-t4. No god draws. Just 5 non-lands and 3 lands.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '309894'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy44651\">blurrymadness</span>\r\n                                (4/23/20